=article-card__link data-tb-link href=/newfoundland-labrador/op-ed-canadas-health-care> <h3 class="article-card__headline text-size--extra-large--sm-up" title="OP-ED: Canada’s health-care crisis is personal, and it's getting harder to believe it can be fixed "><span class=article-card__headline-clamp data-tb-title>OP-ED: Canada’s health-care crisis is personal, and it's getting harder to believe it can be fixed</span></h3> <p class=article-card__excerpt data-tb-description>Canada’s health-care crisis is no longer an abstract policy debate. It’s something you feel in your bones — in the hours spent waiting in emergency rooms, in the anxiety of not having a family doctor, in the helplessness of watching loved ones suffer while the system tells you to wait.</p> </a><div class=article-card__meta-bottom><span class=article-card__time> <span class=article-card__time-clamp data-tb-date> June 30, 2026 </span> </span><span class=article-card__category> <a class=article-card__category-link data-tb-category-link href=/category/newfoundland-labrador/> <span data-evt-skip-click=true data-tb-category>Newfoundland & Labrador</span> </a> </span></div></div><a aria-label="OP-ED: Canada’s health-care crisis is personal, and it's getting harder to believe it can be fixed" class=article-card__image-link data-tb-link href=/newfoundland-labrador/op-ed-canadas-health-care tabindex=-1> <picture class=article-card__image><source data-srcset="https://smartcdn.gprod.postmedia.digital/saltwire/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/health-care-unplash.jpg?quality=90&strip=all&w=344&type=webp&sig=-l-xY5qkpQkOoSaAJRJoYg,
